<br>
Mod rods do *NOT* give more mana back, they convert 225 hp to 175 mana and give less mana back than take to cast, besides the damage.<br>
<br>
In day to day grouping, that's where the robe's use really lies. You don't always have a chanter, do you? So what happens? The mage goes OOM all the time. Sure he has a pet so still contributes, but that's not the point. I blow mana constantly keeping DS up and Malosini-ing targets, abjuration/alteration and I'm specialized in conjuration so mana gets eaten.<br>
<br>
mages specialized in conjuration can get mana back by recasting/reclaiming Monster summoning pets but it takes ages and eats your supply of malachite up VERY fast.<br>
Mages have regeneration from the Phantom Armour spells, so the mana robe rocks.<br>
