<br>
Ahh, but see, when you're baning or regularly nuking a mob and you run out of mana, chances are you won't be able to med because the mob will frenzy on you the second you sit.  Mana Robe is EXTREAMLY useful in these situations, I know from experience that it's squeezed out 3-4 more Banes (and many more nukes pre 60!) in big mob fights.. and that damage really counts.<br>
<br>
Necros don't need these, they have amazing mana regen as it is.  They should be sitting and regenning from the lich process (you can't always heal yourself if you're not pulling mobs and the eye method isn't exactly efficient).  <br>
<br>
Mages are a viable candidate, however they also have nukes.  Rarly do Clerics / should Clerics need mod rods anyway.<br>
<br>
Wizards with Epics are great for Mana Robe and should get priority.  It's especially useful to them.  It's very useful in fights where the extra mana you squeeze out while standing can win the battle.<br>
<br>
Enchanters are decent with it.. but tbh, they only need it for buffing and Mana Robe is hella annoying to click... sitting w/ Mana Song + GoB + C2 is actually faster than standing with robe.<br>
<br>
Anyway, those are my views on it.  Take them how you will! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR>
