Terris - Thule<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udizzykid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dizzy Kid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/3/01 3:46:36 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dizzykid.homestead.com/files/ruluicon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manna Robe &amp; Epic combo</span><hr size=1> I have to absolutely agree with Rombus. ;p Tonight alone, BECUASE of robing myself with epic, I managed to throw out 3 to 4 extra banes a pop in ToV NW.<br>
<br>
The first robe to drop on MT, went to a necro. Day in and day out, he never used it and complained about it's inferior mana regen (compared to Lich) constantly. The only reason he never passed it on was because it was a status symbol at that time.<br>
<br>
Most of the Enchanters on our server didn't want one. They're huge ac/hp/mana freaks, so they preferred CRoAs, at that time (now SoV/Inspiration/Azure).<br>
<br>
Mages; however, are viable competition, imo. However, Mages have complained to me time and time again how limited this robe is of use to them. They regain more mana during CoH downtime with C2/Bard/Sitting then clicking Mana Robe. They've complained several times that they're nukes hardly land on anything and that no one wants their pets. The only times they really use it are when they need to chain cast pets or in fights where their nukes actually land (this includes epic holders too, the epic costs about 300 mana per cast).<br>
<br>
It is my strong belief that loot is not a toy, it's Survival Gear to be able kick the a$$ of the next big thing. It really shouldn't be looked at as &quot;What class can benefit from it the most&quot;, but, &quot;What person will benefit the guild the most by using it&quot;. IMHO, that would be Wizard WITH an epic &gt;&gt; Wizard WITHOUT an epic &gt;&gt; Mage. Wizards WITH an epic will not loose hp and there are several situations where it would benefit their guild. Wizards WITHOUT an epic will loose hp and there are several situations where it would benefit their guild. Mages will loose hp and have limited situations where it would help the guild.<br>
<br>
=) Before you flame me about &quot;class appreciation&quot;, think of it this way...<br>
<br>
Do not think of ways your team can benefit you, but how you can benefit your team. If someone can use an item to benefit the team more then another person, they should get it.<br>
<br>
*edit: small misconception error -- &quot;so they preferred CRoAs.&quot; to  &quot;so they preferred CRoAs, at that time (now SoV/Inspiration/Azure).&quot;<br>
