Well... yeah.  Of course it does.  What on earth would ever make you think that it didn't, unless you happen to have access to ShowEQ numbers which state otherwise (I don't) ??<br>
<br>
If you were sitting (or meditating pre-L35), and were buffed with a mana-regen spell such as c2/clarity, you would get the base mana from meditation in addition to the effect from the mana-regen buff.  If you were standing, and were buffed with a mana-regen spell, you would just get the added mana-regen from the buff plus whatever miniscule mana regen is gained from just standing around... not sure what it is exactly, but it's not much.<br>
<br>
That's my understanding of how mana regen buffs work, at least:  mana-regen buffs such as clarity/c2 are an increase to your *base rate* of mana regen, and your base rate is most definitely affected by whether you are sitting or standing.<br>
<br>
Here's the data on Clarity II:  <br>
<br>
Target: Increase Mana Regeneration Speed (11 Mana Per Tick) <br>
Description: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  This spell increases the amount of mana regained by 11 per tick</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <br>
<br>
Seems pretty self-explanatory and obvious to me, but maybe I'm just over-simplifying things again...<br>
<br>
